# Portfolio Project - LLM Development Guide

## Core Principles

### File Size & Organization

- **MAX 150 LINES PER FILE** - Split larger files into logical modules
- Use type-based organization:
  - `/src/components/layouts/` - Layout components (header, footer, sections)
  - `/src/components/ui/` - shadcn UI components
  - `/src/components/shared/` - Reusable custom components
  - `/src/content/blog/` - Blog MDX files
  - `/src/content/projects/` - Project MDX files
  - `/src/lib/` - Utilities, hooks, helpers
  - `/src/types/` - TypeScript type definitions
- File naming: kebab-case (e.g., `blog-card.tsx`, `project-grid.tsx`)
- Component naming: PascalCase (e.g., `BlogCard`, `ProjectGrid`)

### Code Quality Standards

- **Always apply best practices** - No shortcuts, production-ready code
- **Clear separation of concerns** - Logic, UI, and styles properly separated
- **Semantic HTML** - Use appropriate tags (`<article>`, `<section>`, `<nav>`, etc.)
- **Accessibility first** - WCAG 2.1 AA compliance minimum
- Import order: external → internal → types → styles

## Technology Stack

### Next.js 16 (App Router)

- Use Server Components by default (add `'use client'` only when needed)
- Server Actions for mutations, not API routes
- Dynamic metadata for SEO (`generateMetadata`)
- Streaming with `<Suspense>` for better UX
- Route groups for organization: `(routes)`, `(marketing)`

### TypeScript

- Strict mode enabled - no `any` types without justification
- Use interfaces for props, types for unions/intersections
- Proper JSDoc comments for complex props
- Export types alongside components

```typescript
interface BlogCardProps {
  /** The blog post title */
  title: string;
  /** ISO date string */
  publishedAt: string;
  slug: string;
}
```

### Tailwind CSS & Semantic Colors

- Use semantic color system from `globals.css`
- Prefer `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `border-border` over direct colors
- Custom utilities in `@layer utilities` when needed
- Responsive design: mobile-first approach
- Dark mode support using `class` strategy

### shadcn/ui Components

- **Use shadcn MCP to search and add components** - Don't build from scratch
- Search via MCP: `mcp_shadcn_search_items_in_registries`
- View examples: `mcp_shadcn_get_item_examples_from_registries`
- Customize in `/src/components/ui/` after installation
- Prefer composition over creating new UI primitives

### Motion (Animation Library)

- **Subtle, professional animations only** - No excessive motion
- Use motion MCP for CSS spring/bounce generation
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` media query
- Animation durations:
  - Quick/Snappy: ~0.2s
  - Normal: 0.3-0.4s
  - Slow/Dramatic: ~1s (rarely used)
- Generate springs via MCP: `mcp_motion_generate-css-spring`
- Default spring: `bounce: 0.2, duration: 0.4`

```typescript
// Example: Subtle fade-in animation
<motion.div
  initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 20 }}
  animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
  transition={{ duration: 0.4, ease: [0.25, 0.1, 0.25, 1] }}
>
```

