## Component Guidelines

### Server vs Client Components

- **Default: Server Component** (better performance, SEO)
- Use `'use client'` when:
  - Using React hooks (`useState`, `useEffect`, etc.)
  - Adding event listeners (`onClick`, `onChange`)
  - Using browser APIs
  - Working with motion animations

### Component Structure

```typescript
// Server Component (default)
interface HeroProps {
  title: string;
  subtitle: string;
}

export function Hero({ title, subtitle }: HeroProps) {
  return (
    <section className="container mx-auto px-4">
      <h1>{title}</h1>
      <p>{subtitle}</p>
    </section>
  );
}

// Client Component (when needed)
'use client';

import { useState } from 'react';

export function InteractiveCard() {
  const [isHovered, setIsHovered] = useState(false);
  // ...
}
```

### Props Best Practices

- Destructure props in function signature
- Provide default values when appropriate
- Use optional chaining for nested properties
- Type children properly: `React.ReactNode`

## Performance & Optimization

### Images

- Use Next.js `<Image>` component always
- Provide `width` and `height` or `fill` prop
- Use `priority` for above-fold images
- Lazy load below-fold content

### Fonts

- Use `next/font` for optimal loading
- Preload critical fonts
- Use font-display: swap

### Code Splitting

- Dynamic imports for heavy components
- Lazy load modals, carousels, maps

```typescript
const HeavyChart = dynamic(() => import("@/components/charts/heavy-chart"));
```

## Accessibility Requirements

- All images have descriptive `alt` text
- Proper heading hierarchy (h1 → h2 → h3)
- Interactive elements are keyboard accessible
- Focus states visible and clear
- ARIA labels for icon-only buttons
- Form inputs have associated labels
- Color contrast ratio ≥ 4.5:1

## SEO Best Practices

- Unique `<title>` and `<meta description>` per page
- Open Graph tags for social sharing
- Structured data (JSON-LD) for blog posts
- Sitemap generation
- robots.txt configuration
- Canonical URLs to prevent duplicates

