## Workflow

1. **Starting new feature**: Check if shadcn component exists via MCP
2. **Creating animations**: Use motion MCP to generate spring/bounce CSS
3. **Adding content**: Create MDX file with proper frontmatter
4. **Before commit**: Run lint and format checks
5. **Component growing**: Split at 150 lines - extract logic/sub-components

## Common Patterns

### Blog Post Card

```typescript
interface BlogPostCardProps {
  title: string;
  description: string;
  publishedAt: string;
  slug: string;
  tags: string[];
}

export function BlogPostCard({ title, description, publishedAt, slug, tags }: BlogPostCardProps) {
  return (
    <article className="group">
      <Link href={`/blog/${slug}`}>
        <h3 className="font-semibold">{title}</h3>
        <p className="text-muted-foreground">{description}</p>
        <time dateTime={publishedAt}>{formatDate(publishedAt)}</time>
        <div className="flex gap-2">
          {tags.map(tag => <span key={tag}>{tag}</span>)}
        </div>
      </Link>
    </article>
  );
}
```

